<div id="review_616437711" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/616437711" />
    <a title="Shannon" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1715547-shannon"><img alt="Shannon" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1238187851p2/1715547.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/616437711?book_show_action=true">May 15, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Shannon" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Shannon" href="/user/show/1715547-shannon">Shannon</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1715547-shannon?shelf=historical-fiction">historical-fiction</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
                  <em>
                    This review has been hidden because it contains spoilers. To view it,
                    <a href="#" onclick="Effect.toggle(&#39;reviewTextContainer616437711&#39;); return false;">click here.</a>
                  </em>
              <span id="reviewTextContainer616437711" class="readable"
                    style="display:none"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8013451066004273740">A novel about the life of a young Indian widow who flees her tragic life after the death of her old husband to Africa as an indentured worker. I found the characters of Usha and her father to be most believable. I did have difficulties with Rothwell who did his best to treat everyone well. But felt that he and his wife were truly caricatures. Where I had difficulty was that in his efforts to make the lives of the coolies better he totally missed the mark in understanding his friend Krishnan and </span>
  <span id="freeText8013451066004273740" style="display:none">A novel about the life of a young Indian widow who flees her tragic life after the death of her old husband to Africa as an indentured worker. I found the characters of Usha and her father to be most believable. I did have difficulties with Rothwell who did his best to treat everyone well. But felt that he and his wife were truly caricatures. Where I had difficulty was that in his efforts to make the lives of the coolies better he totally missed the mark in understanding his friend Krishnan and ultimately Usha herself. Also, I did not feel that the wife was fleshed out well enough to be believable. I also felt that other characters were dropped and could have been woven in further (e.g. Royston)<br /><br />The ending was very abrupt and although was probably the most appropriate of endings I would have liked a little more lead up. Perhaps its a good thing that I was left wanting more.<br /><br />All in all a good book and I am glad to have read it. </span>
  <a data-text-id="8013451066004273740" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


